.TH "calc_dsc_bpp_x16" 9 "calc_dsc_bpp_x16" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
calc_dsc_bpp_x16 \- retrieve the dsc bits per pixel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" calc_dsc_bpp_x16
.BI "(u32 stream_bandwidth_kbps "  ","
.BI "u32 pix_clk_100hz "  ","
.BI "u32 bpp_increment_div "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "stream_bandwidth_kbps" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "pix_clk_100hz" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "bpp_increment_div" 12
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calculate the total of bits per pixel for DSC configuration.

\fInote\fP This calculation requires float point operation, most of it executes
under kernel_fpu_{begin,end}.
